  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DatabaseException
    Thrown when there's an error while executing any of the Database methods.
    DistributedLock.ReentrantException
    Thrown when the thread tries to reacquire the same lock.
    Query.NoFieldException
    Thrown when a key used within a query references a field that doesn't exist.
    Query.NoIndexException
    Thrown when a key used within a query references a field that's not indexed.
    RecoverableDatabaseException
    Thrown when there's a recoverable error while executing any of the Database methods.
    SqlDatabaseException
    Thrown when there's an error while executing any of the SqlDatabase methods.
    SqlDatabaseException.ReadTimeout  
    UnsupportedIndexException  
    UnsupportedPredicateException
    Thrown when use of an predicate isn't supported.
    UnsupportedSorterException
    Thrown when use of a sorter isn't supported.
    ValidationException
    Thrown when there are invalid states that are about to be saved to the database.
